qas.question: A special memory cell of a CPU is called what?
A register of a CPU keeps track of what?

answers.text: which location in memory the next instruction is to be read from

qas.question: What is a component that all CPUs have?

context: A key component common to all CPUs is <a2_0>the program counter<a2_0/>, a special memory cell (<a0_0>a register<a0_0/>) that keeps track of <a1_0>which location in memory the next instruction is to be read from<a1_0/>.
